<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-650-988  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 650 988.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  July 16 1990 n599 p15(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Foundation aims to 'civilize digital domain'. (formation ofElectronic Frontier Foundation to safeguard the civil rights ofcomputer users)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Robinson, Brian.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Concern for the civil rights of users, especially those in theinnovating forefront of the industry, has sparked the formation ofa new organization: Electronic Frontier Foundation (EFF).andP;  EFFsupports laws that prosecute perpetrators of computer crimes, yetit wants to define clearly the boundaries of free speech andconstitutional rights and liberties as they pertain to the user.andO;EFF aims to reduce the fear permeating the public's view ofcomputers and their power through educational activities, lobbyingpolicymakers, the raising of public awareness about civilliberties issues and the encouragement and support for thedevelopment of new tools.andP;  As a first step, EFF has awarded a$275,000 grant to Computer Professionals for Social Responsibilityto host a series of symposia for lawmakers, users, the FBI andmembers of the computer security community.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Electronic Frontier FoundationLegal IssuesUser NeedsGoals and ObjectivesComputer Professionals for Social ResponsibilitySocial IssuesNonprofit Organization.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>